{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the International Society for Technology in Education (ISTE) in the United States offered a recent definition in 2018: CT is using the core principles and practices of computer science to solve vague, complex, and open-ended problems.",
    "The association also highlighted that CT, as a composite ability, includes creativity, algorithmic thinking, critical thinking, problem-solving, and collaborative thinking (ISTE, 2018).",
    "Chinese scholars have also interpreted CT from various perspectives.",
    "Tracing back to the early 1990s, scholar Chongfu Huang first introduced the concept of \"computational thinking\" in an academic paper.",
    "He focused on the computational simulation of the thinking process, advocating that this process embodies CT."
  ]
}